{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep3_neutral_pct",
    "description": "Map how pool_neutral_pct reshapes the economic zone boundaries found in targeted_sweep1 and targeted_sweep2. pool_neutral_pct controls what fraction of pool hashrate follows price signals rather than ideology. It has been fixed at 30% across all 93 prior targeted scenarios.\nStructural effect of neutral_pct on pool assignment (commit=0.50):\n  neutral=10%: v27-committed=38.1% (Foundry+MARA+Luxor+Ocean)\n               v26-committed=39.0% (AntPool+F2Pool+ViaBTC)\n               neutral=9.3% (SpiderPool only)\n  neutral=20%: v27-committed=34.6% (Foundry+MARA)\n               v26-committed=31.3% (Luxor+Ocean+AntPool+F2Pool)\n               neutral=20.5% (ViaBTC+Spider)\n  neutral=30%: v27-committed=30.0% (Foundry only)      [baseline]\n               v26-committed=35.9% (MARA+Luxor+Ocean+AntPool+F2Pool)\n               neutral=20.5% (ViaBTC+Spider)\n  neutral=40%: v27-committed=30.0% (Foundry only)\n               v26-committed=25.0% (MARA+Luxor+Ocean+AntPool)\n               neutral=31.4% (F2Pool+ViaBTC+Spider)\n  neutral=50%: v27-committed=30.0% (Foundry only)\n               v26-committed=8.1%  (MARA+Luxor+Ocean only)\n               neutral=48.3% (AntPool+F2Pool+ViaBTC+Spider)\n\nKey hypothesis: the inversion zone (v26 wins at econ=0.60-0.70 despite v27 economic majority) is driven by the committed v26 bloc being large enough to resist economic pressure. As neutral_pct increases from 30% to 50%, the v26 bloc shrinks from 35.9% to 8.1% \u2014 the inversion should weaken and eventually disappear. Conversely, at neutral_pct=10% the blocs are nearly balanced and dynamics may be more contested.\nCross-check: neutral_pct=30 row should exactly replicate the hash=0.25 column from targeted_sweep2 (commit=0.50, all other params identical).\nGrid: 5 neutral levels \u00d7 7 economic levels = 35 scenarios Duration: ~18h 40m at 32 min/scenario\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep3_neutral_pct.yaml",
